<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-9382] Inconsistent support for [Bb]oolean properties</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-9382</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In addition to issues noted in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-5245&quot; title=&quot;Inconsistency with accessing issers as properties&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-5245&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;GROOVY-5245&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-6097&quot; title=&quot;Using super.propertyName gives a MissingMethodException when the property is a boolean and uses the &amp;quot;isPropertyName&amp;quot; naming convention.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-6097&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;GROOVY-6097&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, consider the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-groovy&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;Pogo {
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Boolean&lt;/span&gt; b = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;
}
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; pogo = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Pogo()
println pogo.b &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// prints &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;println pogo.getB() &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// prints &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;println pogo.isB() &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throws&lt;/span&gt; MissingPropertyException&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If &lt;tt&gt;@TypeChecked&lt;/tt&gt; is added, no STC error for &lt;tt&gt;pogo.isB()&lt;/tt&gt;.  If &lt;tt&gt;@CompileStatic&lt;/tt&gt; is added, no STC error for &lt;tt&gt;pogo.isB()&lt;/tt&gt; and exception changes to NoSuchMethodError.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d prefer a Boolean property could be accessed using an &quot;is&quot; method.   If the scenario is reversed (class with only &lt;tt&gt;Boolean isB()&lt;/tt&gt; method), the property expression &lt;tt&gt;pogo.b&lt;/tt&gt; is supported.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
